{
  "name": "2003-sars-electronics-supply-chain-ec0375",
  "title": "Asian Virus Casts Shadow Over Supply Chain: SARS Impact on Asia/Pacific Semiconductor and Electronics Manufacturing",
  "description": "Aberdeen Group analyst report (Russ Craig and Peter Kastner) excerpted by PlanetAnalog/EBN on April 16, 2003, examining the potential impact of the SARS epidemic on the PRC- and Taiwan-centered global electronics supply chain. The authors quantify Asia/Pacific's 37% share of 2002 semiconductor consumption ($52B), document early SARS clusters in Guangdong, Shenzhen, Guangzhou, Hong Kong, Singapore, and Taiwan, and assess the vulnerability of dependable component supply \u2014 particularly for no-second-source items like PRC-made AC/DC power supplies \u2014 should quarantines extend. The report ends with a prescient warning that investor confidence in the PRC will take years to rebuild given government opacity about the outbreak.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-19",
